you might've been able to
make it as a top otoko-yaku!

00:10:45.812 --> 00:10:47.439 position:50% align:center
[RISA] That was the day
I learned that only girls

00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:51.276 position:50% align:center
like Hijiri had a chance of
becoming a top musume-yaku.

00:10:51.359 --> 00:10:54.571 position:50% align:center
Girls with angelic faces
and a mean streak to boot.

00:10:56.156 --> 00:10:59.993 position:50% align:center
I still don't get it!
Why can't I play Lady Oscar?

00:11:00.076 --> 00:11:01.619 position:50% align:center
Oh, wait, I know!

00:11:01.703 --> 00:11:03.371 position:50% align:center
Before the welcome ceremony,

00:11:03.455 --> 00:11:05.957 position:50% align:center
you stood under the
cherry tree, didn't you?

00:11:06.041 --> 00:11:07.042 position:50% align:center
Yes?

00:11:08.084 --> 00:11:09.627 position:50% align:center
[RISA]
That explains it, then.

00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:11.963 position:50% align:center
No one who's stood underneath
the cherry tree before

00:11:12.047 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
starting school here has ever
become one of Kouka's top stars.

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:17.719 position:50% align:center
It's well known
the tree is cursed.

00:11:19.262 --> 00:11:20.513 position:50% align:center
[SARASA]
So, that's it?

00:11:20.597 --> 00:11:22.015 position:50% align:center
'Fraid so.

00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:23.808 position:50% align:center
[SARASA]
I know what to do.

00:11:23.892 --> 00:11:26.102 position:50% align:center
I'll have to prove
that curse is fake!

00:11:27.645 --> 00:11:30.899 position:50% align:center
You know, I couldn't even
be here if I was a guy.

00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:33.985 position:50% align:center
I was born as a girl instead,
and then I got chosen

00:11:34.069 --> 00:11:36.488 position:50% align:center
to be a part of this.

00:11:36.571 --> 00:11:38.406 position:50% align:center
But I don't believe there
should be such a thing

00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:42.118 position:50% align:center
as absolutes when it
comes to can or can't.

00:11:42.202 --> 00:11:44.496 position:50% align:center
It isn't right.

00:11:44.579 --> 00:11:47.082 position:50% align:center
So there's no way I'm gonna
let that curse hold me back!

00:11:50.669 --> 00:11:52.087 position:50% align:center
Well, then.

00:11:52.170 --> 00:11:55.298 position:50% align:center
I guess no one knows what you're
capable of but you, right?

00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:57.425 position:50% align:center
Give it a shot.

00:11:57.509 --> 00:11:58.468 position:50% align:center
I will!

00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:00.720 position:50% align:center
[RISA]
I will, too.

00:12:01.596 --> 00:12:03.723 position:50% align:center
It's almost time
for class. C'mon.

00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:08.978 position:50% align:center
I'll help you out so we can
finish up a little bit quicker.

00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:10.605 position:50% align:center
[SARASA]
Huh?

00:12:10.689 --> 00:12:11.898 position:50% align:center
Big Sis!

00:12:12.691 --> 00:12:15.068 position:50% align:center
[SARASA]
Heh! Cleaning complete!

00:12:15.151 --> 00:12:16.277 position:50% align:center
Good, there you are!

00:12:16.361 --> 00:12:18.530 position:50% align:center
I was starting to get
a little worried!

00:12:18.613 --> 00:12:20.490 position:50% align:center
And here I thought
you'd messed up again.

00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:21.741 position:50% align:center
You were worried about me?

00:12:21.825 --> 00:12:23.118 position:50% align:center
No. Not you.

00:12:23.201 --> 00:12:25.495 position:50% align:center
If one of us first-years messes
up, the second-years

00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:28.123 position:50% align:center
will yell at all of us
as if we'd all done it.

00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:30.291 position:50% align:center
Your advisor seemed kinda
strict, so hopefully you

00:12:30.375 --> 00:12:31.209 position:50% align:center
did okay.

00:12:31.292 --> 00:12:32.627 position:50% align:center
Prove me right, please.

00:12:32.711 --> 00:12:33.878 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:36.214 position:50% align:center
Risa certainly doesn't
mince words or anything,

00:12:36.297 --> 00:12:37.757 position:50% align:center
but I think she's really nice!

00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:39.592 position:50% align:center
She definitely messed up!

00:12:39.676 --> 00:12:42.595 position:50% align:center
Yeah, our advisors were
pretty scary, too, right?

00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:44.764 position:50% align:center
I'll say they were!
Mine stared daggers at me

00:12:44.848 --> 00:12:46.683 position:50% align:center
when I accidentally
fumbled the broom!

00:12:46.766 --> 00:12:49.185 position:50% align:center
Kouka is just so
competitive and intense.

00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:51.312 position:50% align:center
But your advisor
seemed really sweet, Ai!

00:12:51.396 --> 00:12:53.732 position:50% align:center
I think you might've won
the lottery on that, huh?

00:12:56.109 --> 00:12:57.110 position:50% align:center
I doubt it.

00:12:58.653 --> 00:13:00.613 position:50% align:center
[TAKEI]
So? How was our Lady Oscar?

00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:03.241 position:50% align:center
Nothing special.
She's still just a child.

00:13:04.743 --> 00:13:06.745 position:50% align:center
Hang on, what's happening, Risa?

00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:08.413 position:50% align:center
You actually look happy!

00:13:08.496 --> 00:13:10.331 position:50% align:center
Must be rough on you, Hijiri.

00:13:10.415 --> 00:13:12.292 position:50% align:center
People seem to think
Naracchi could be a top

00:13:12.375 --> 00:13:14.210 position:50% align:center
musume-yaku one day.

00:13:14.294 --> 00:13:17.380 position:50% align:center
I'm not quite sure where
you got that idea,

00:13:17.464 --> 00:13:19.341 position:50% align:center
but you are mistaken.

00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:20.967 position:50% align:center
No motivation.

00:13:21.051 --> 00:13:22.761 position:50% align:center
That's Naracchi's thing.

00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:25.221 position:50% align:center
[RISA] Well, it'll be
interesting to see how it goes.

00:13:25.305 --> 00:13:27.599 position:50% align:center
Who knows what wind
might lift her sails?

00:13:27.682 --> 00:13:29.351 position:50% align:center
After all, the future's
wide open.

00:13:42.947 --> 00:13:44.157 position:50% align:center
Hey! What the--?

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:45.825 position:50% align:center
What do you want, Kouzaburou?

00:13:45.909 --> 00:13:47.494 position:50% align:center
Aren't those Sarasa's tweets?

00:13:47.577 --> 00:13:49.079 position:50% align:center
Lemme see.

00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:51.414 position:50% align:center
What? It's super important. I
need to make sure you and Sarasa

00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:53.500 position:50% align:center
are keeping it all
wholesome and above board.

00:13:53.583 --> 00:13:55.460 position:50% align:center
As if that's any
of your business!

00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.712 position:50% align:center
Akiya, do me a little favor.

00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:59.547 position:50% align:center
remind me who bought
that tablet for you.

00:14:01.591 --> 00:14:03.051 position:50% align:center
[KOUZABUROU]
Hmm.

00:14:03.134 --> 00:14:05.303 position:50% align:center
So, she learned how to
clean a classroom today.

00:14:05.387 --> 00:14:07.889 position:50% align:center
Under the tutelage of
a cool Latin beauty.

00:14:07.972 --> 00:14:10.850 position:50% align:center
I didn't know that, I guess
I haven't read that far.

00:14:10.934 --> 00:14:13.186 position:50% align:center
[KOUZABUROU] Come on,
wipe that look off your face.

00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:14.979 position:50% align:center
It does you no good.

00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:17.565 position:50% align:center
Your most dedicated fans
are older women.

00:14:17.649 --> 00:14:20.777 position:50% align:center
Watch the attitude or
you'll lose them all.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.571 position:50% align:center
Sarasa's turned 15, now, huh?

00:14:23.655 --> 00:14:25.448 position:50% align:center
Wow, she must be getting big.

00:14:25.532 --> 00:14:26.950 position:50% align:center
She definitely is.

00:14:27.033 --> 00:14:29.244 position:50% align:center
And she's already taller than
me, if you can believe it.

00:14:29.327 --> 00:14:31.079 position:50% align:center
Amazing.

00:14:31.162 --> 00:14:33.456 position:50% align:center
She was so tiny back in
the day, when you two

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:36.209 position:50% align:center
were both taking
dance lessons here.

00:14:36.292 --> 00:14:39.129 position:50% align:center
I kinda wish that we
could've kept her around.

00:14:39.212 --> 00:14:40.839 position:50% align:center
So, Kobe, huh?

00:14:40.922 --> 00:14:43.216 position:50% align:center
maybe I'll go sneak a peek
at her one of these days.

00:14:43.299 --> 00:14:45.969 position:50% align:center
That's creepy-stalker territory.
Don't be weird.

00:14:46.052 --> 00:14:47.429 position:50% align:center
By the way, Akiya.

00:14:47.512 --> 00:14:48.972 position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:14:49.055 --> 00:14:51.224 position:50% align:center
Coming to you for this every
time is getting really annoying.

00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:53.018 position:50% align:center
So, if you wouldn't mind,

00:14:53.101 --> 00:14:54.894 position:50% align:center
could you gimme the
password for this account?

00:15:00.817 --> 00:15:03.278 position:50% align:center
[ANDOU]
I'm Mr. Andou. I teach acting.

00:15:03.361 --> 00:15:04.738 position:50% align:center
So, then...

00:15:04.821 --> 00:15:06.990 position:50% align:center
I'd planned to do a short intro
to Shakespearean dramas,

00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:09.617 position:50% align:center
but now I've changed my mind.

00:15:09.701 --> 00:15:12.495 position:50% align:center
Let's do a round of
introductions instead.

00:15:12.579 --> 00:15:14.956 position:50% align:center
Mister Andou, forgive me
for saying this

00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.208 position:50% align:center
and speaking out of turn
on the first day of class,

00:15:17.292 --> 00:15:19.502 position:50% align:center
but should we really be
wasting time on that?

00:15:19.586 --> 00:15:20.754 position:50% align:center
I wanna!

00:15:20.837 --> 00:15:22.505 position:50% align:center
I'd be happy to volunteer
and start us off!

00:15:22.589 --> 00:15:24.257 position:50% align:center
Wait. Slow it down.

00:15:24.341 --> 00:15:26.885 position:50% align:center
This is no normal school,
as you all are well aware.

00:15:26.968 --> 00:15:28.845 position:50% align:center
'Cause there,
you've got choices.

00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:31.431 position:50% align:center
When you graduate from there,
you can go on to college,

00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:34.392 position:50% align:center
or find a job, take an
apprenticeship, get married,

00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.269 position:50% align:center
move away, et cetera.

00:15:36.353 --> 00:15:39.397 position:50% align:center
But here, you've only
got two options:

00:15:39.481 --> 00:15:41.024 position:50% align:center
To sink or swim.

00:15:41.107 --> 00:15:43.485 position:50% align:center
To stay with Kouka
or to give up.

00:15:43.568 --> 00:15:45.111 position:50% align:center
Once you graduate
from this program,

00:15:45.195 --> 00:15:47.113 position:50% align:center
you'll be joining
the Kouka Troupe.

00:15:47.197 --> 00:15:48.406 position:50% align:center
Know what that means?

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:51.034 position:50% align:center
You're basically
stuck together forever.

00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:52.869 position:50% align:center
So, I think it'd be a good
idea for you to learn more

00:15:52.952 --> 00:15:55.705 position:50% align:center
about each other and
start getting along,

00:15:55.789 --> 00:15:57.624 position:50% align:center
a little earlier in your tenure.

00:15:57.707 --> 00:15:59.417 position:50% align:center
Wouldn't you agree?

00:15:59.501 --> 00:16:00.877 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Very well, Mister Andou.

00:16:00.960 --> 00:16:02.253 position:50% align:center
Then, as our class
representative,

00:16:02.337 --> 00:16:04.255 position:50% align:center
I'll start with
my introduction.

00:16:04.339 --> 00:16:06.216 position:50% align:center
Do it, Miss Priss.

00:16:06.299 --> 00:16:08.426 position:50% align:center
Sawa Sugimoto, 16.

00:16:08.510 --> 00:16:11.471 position:50% align:center
My family runs a well-known
ballet studio in Tokyo,

00:16:11.554 --> 00:16:14.265 position:50% align:center
where I studied dance
rigorously from a young age.

00:16:14.349 --> 00:16:16.518 position:50% align:center
They'd considered sending
me abroad for ballet,

00:16:16.601 --> 00:16:19.688 position:50% align:center
but, as my life's goal is to
perform musical theater,

00:16:19.771 --> 00:16:23.441 position:50% align:center
I applied to attend the Kouka
school instead of going away.

00:16:23.525 --> 00:16:25.402 position:50% align:center
I'm very honored to be here.

00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:26.653 position:50% align:center
[SARASA laughs]

00:16:28.196 --> 00:16:30.281 position:50% align:center
Kaoru Hoshino. I'm 18.

00:16:30.365 --> 00:16:33.576 position:50% align:center
In my family, musume-yaku
is a tradition.

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.036 position:50% align:center
But because I've been
blessed with height,

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:38.123 position:50% align:center
I'm going to play male roles
as the first otoko-yaku.

00:16:38.206 --> 00:16:41.084 position:50% align:center
I'd like to add that I also
want to be an otoko-yaku!

00:16:41.167 --> 00:16:42.627 position:50% align:center
All right, let's calm down.

00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:44.754 position:50% align:center
I'm Chiaki Sawada!

00:16:44.838 --> 00:16:46.214 position:50% align:center
I'm Chika Sawada!

00:16:46.297 --> 00:16:49.009 position:50% align:center
Chika got in last year,
but I wasn't quite as lucky

00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:50.593 position:50% align:center
and we couldn't be apart.

00:16:50.677 --> 00:16:53.346 position:50% align:center
I decided to wait a year, hoping
that we could get in together,

00:16:53.430 --> 00:16:55.348 position:50% align:center
and it worked out perfectly.

00:16:55.432 --> 00:16:57.892 position:50% align:center
[YAMADA]
Uh, my name is Ayako Yamada.

00:16:57.976 --> 00:17:00.770 position:50% align:center
I've loved Kouka ever
since I was really small.

00:17:00.854 --> 00:17:03.690 position:50% align:center
Honestly, I can't believe
I actually got in.

00:17:03.773 --> 00:17:06.568 position:50% align:center
So, I'm going to give
Kouka my all!

00:17:06.651 --> 00:17:09.070 position:50% align:center
I'm Sarasa Watanabe, I'm 15!

00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:12.574 position:50% align:center
I've dreamed of playing Lady
Oscar ever since I can remember.

00:17:12.657 --> 00:17:15.368 position:50% align:center
Yes, we know, and you're
going to be a top star, too.

00:17:15.452 --> 00:17:18.455 position:50% align:center
Right! I love anime, and manga,
and period pieces,

00:17:18.538 --> 00:17:20.665 position:50% align:center
and I live in Asakusa
with my Grandpa Ken!

00:17:20.749 --> 00:17:23.168 position:50% align:center
He makes tatami mats.
And he's done it forever!

00:17:23.251 --> 00:17:25.337 position:50% align:center
Oh, and we have a little
cat named Nono!

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:27.505 position:50% align:center
She's super cute, and her
nose is always twitching--

00:17:27.589 --> 00:17:30.133 position:50% align:center
You can tell us more
about your cat later.

00:17:30.216 --> 00:17:32.385 position:50% align:center
All right, last one.

00:17:32.469 --> 00:17:35.347 position:50% align:center
Ai Narata. I'm 16.

00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:37.682 position:50% align:center
I've done ballet
since I was young.

00:17:37.766 --> 00:17:40.352 position:50% align:center
I was taught by my uncle,
Taichi Narata.

00:17:40.435 --> 00:17:42.771 position:50% align:center
He works here as
a ballet teacher.

00:17:42.854 --> 00:17:44.731 position:50% align:center
That's all.

00:17:44.814 --> 00:17:47.025 position:50% align:center
Seriously? That's so not all.

00:17:51.488 --> 00:17:53.823 position:50% align:center
My mother is Kimiko Narata.

00:17:53.907 --> 00:17:56.076 position:50% align:center
I was formerly in JPX48.

00:17:56.159 --> 00:17:58.244 position:50% align:center
I was voted 13th.

00:17:58.328 --> 00:18:00.205 position:50% align:center
And then, I quit.

00:18:00.288 --> 00:18:02.874 position:50% align:center
No, they made me quit,
so I came here.

00:18:02.957 --> 00:18:04.125 position:50% align:center
That's all.

00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:09.381 position:50% align:center
Whoa, hold the phone,
were you really a JPX idol?

00:18:09.464 --> 00:18:11.091 position:50% align:center
I had no idea. That's so cool!

00:18:11.174 --> 00:18:13.718 position:50% align:center
Well, that's that. Now,
let's head out for our tour

00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:15.887 position:50% align:center
of the Kouka Theatre's
backstage, yeah?

00:18:15.970 --> 00:18:17.055 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasp]

00:18:17.138 --> 00:18:18.515 position:50% align:center
Backstage?

00:18:18.598 --> 00:18:20.058 position:50% align:center
Yep, you're in luck.

00:18:20.141 --> 00:18:22.852 position:50% align:center
I got special permission to
take you all on a tour today.

00:18:22.936 --> 00:18:25.105 position:50% align:center
You'll soon see that the
stage doesn't just belong

00:18:25.188 --> 00:18:26.523 position:50% align:center
to its actresses.

00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.525 position:50% align:center
Isn't this the best
surprise, Ai-Ai?

00:18:30.819 --> 00:18:34.239 position:50% align:center
[ANDOU] Here's our first stop,
the costumers.

00:18:34.322 --> 00:18:36.574 position:50% align:center
[YAMADA] The embellishments
are all hand-sewn!

00:18:36.658 --> 00:18:37.992 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow!

00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:41.037 position:50% align:center
My gosh! Those huge feathers!
I'd know them anywhere.

00:18:41.121 --> 00:18:43.623 position:50% align:center
They're worn by the top
otoko-yaku of the Winter Troupe,

00:18:43.707 --> 00:18:45.458 position:50% align:center
Sou Kazahana!

00:18:45.542 --> 00:18:48.211 position:50% align:center
[gasps] They're too incredible.

00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:50.755 position:50% align:center
I can't even look!

00:18:50.839 --> 00:18:52.966 position:50% align:center
Ah! It's the bunny girl costume!

00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:58.388 position:50% align:center
Wow! Would you check out this
mountain of dresses, you guys?

00:18:58.471 --> 00:19:00.724 position:50% align:center
Mon dieu!
Does Rose Bertin work here?

00:19:00.807 --> 00:19:02.976 position:50% align:center
Because I feel just
like Rosalie!

00:19:03.059 --> 00:19:04.728 position:50% align:center
Don't you agree, Ai?

00:19:04.811 --> 00:19:06.396 position:50% align:center
Right, let's move on.

00:19:06.479 --> 00:19:07.897 position:50% align:center
What do we say, people?

00:19:07.981 --> 00:19:09.274 position:50% align:center
It's been a pleasure!

00:19:09.357 --> 00:19:10.900 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much for having us!

00:19:12.068 --> 00:19:13.528 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey, it's Naracchi!

00:19:13.611 --> 00:19:15.947 position:50% align:center
Yeah, she sure does
stand out, doesn't she?

00:19:16.031 --> 00:19:17.991 position:50% align:center
I'll have to brag
to my daughter.

00:19:18.074 --> 00:19:20.618 position:50% align:center
Did you get a look at that
other stand-out, though?

00:19:20.702 --> 00:19:23.621 position:50% align:center
The one with the sparkling eyes,
towering over all the others.

00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:27.125 position:50% align:center
[ANDOU] This is where
the set gets built.

00:19:27.208 --> 00:19:30.045 position:50% align:center
Scenery does their work
here, right backstage.

00:19:30.128 --> 00:19:32.088 position:50% align:center
[YAMADA]
That sure is a long brush!

00:19:32.172 --> 00:19:34.215 position:50% align:center
[HOSHINO] Yeah, I've
never seen one like that.

00:19:34.299 --> 00:19:36.217 position:50% align:center
[SARASA]
Whoa, it's all Styrofoam!

00:19:36.301 --> 00:19:37.886 position:50% align:center
But it looks so real!

00:19:37.969 --> 00:19:39.596 position:50% align:center
Hey, that's good to hear.

00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:42.098 position:50% align:center
C'mon, Miss Watanabe,
don't get in their way.

00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:44.100 position:50% align:center
[SET BOSS A]
It's all good, Mamoru.

00:19:44.184 --> 00:19:46.269 position:50% align:center
Gettin' praised by future
actresses helps us all

00:19:46.353 --> 00:19:48.730 position:50% align:center
feel motivated to work
a bit harder, you know?

00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:51.399 position:50% align:center
Great! I'm gonna be
a top star one day!

00:19:51.483 --> 00:19:54.361 position:50% align:center
When I get there, I hope you'll
make me an awesome set!

00:19:54.444 --> 00:19:55.779 position:50% align:center
There she goes again.

00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:57.822 position:50% align:center
[laughing]
Well, all right!

00:19:57.906 --> 00:20:00.492 position:50% align:center
There ain't no goin' back on
a bold statement like that,

00:20:00.575 --> 00:20:01.743 position:50% align:center
is there?

00:20:01.826 --> 00:20:03.828 position:50% align:center
We'll be waitin' for ya!
You better believe it!

00:20:03.912 --> 00:20:06.247 position:50% align:center
Yay! We got ourselves a deal!

00:20:06.331 --> 00:20:07.957 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much for your time!

00:20:25.058 --> 00:20:28.269 position:50% align:center
What're you doing?! Watanabe!
Don't go through there!

00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:31.106 position:50% align:center
Not one more step!

00:20:31.189 --> 00:20:32.524 position:50% align:center
That's the stage door!

00:20:58.758 --> 00:20:59.843 position:50% align:center
[ANDOU]
Miss Watanabe!

00:20:59.926 --> 00:21:01.594 position:50% align:center
Get back here, right now!

00:21:01.678 --> 00:21:05.015 position:50% align:center
And don't you dare attempt to
walk out on the silver bridge!

00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:06.391 position:50% align:center
What's that?

00:21:06.474 --> 00:21:07.851 position:50% align:center
The bit out front.

00:21:07.934 --> 00:21:10.103 position:50% align:center
The part of the apron that's
separated from the stage.

00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:12.772 position:50% align:center
Only Kouka's most prestigious
stars are ever allowed

00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:15.108 position:50% align:center
to cross that bridge.

00:21:15.191 --> 00:21:18.028 position:50% align:center
[HOSHINO] Yeah, only the top
otoko-yaku and musume-yaku

00:21:18.111 --> 00:21:20.822 position:50% align:center
and a handful of others
get to experience that.

00:21:20.905 --> 00:21:23.074 position:50% align:center
So, it's this huge honor.

00:21:23.158 --> 00:21:24.284 position:50% align:center
Our goal.

00:21:24.367 --> 00:21:27.287 position:50% align:center
We all want to
stand there one day.

00:21:27.370 --> 00:21:28.747 position:50% align:center
The silver bridge.

00:21:33.501 --> 00:21:35.587 position:50% align:center
[LIGHTING A]
Huh. Someone's out on stage.

00:21:35.670 --> 00:21:37.672 position:50% align:center
[LIGHTING B] Judging from the
height, it's probably Yama.

00:21:37.756 --> 00:21:39.424 position:50% align:center
Pop a light on him
and let's see.

00:21:48.683 --> 00:21:51.186 position:50% align:center
[ANDOU] If you want to become
one of Kouka's top stars,

00:21:51.269 --> 00:21:54.856 position:50% align:center
it'll take hard work, talent,
lots of star quality,

00:21:54.939 --> 00:21:58.234 position:50% align:center
and, of course, enough luck to
be given the right chance.

00:22:00.737 --> 00:22:03.615 position:50% align:center
[AI] Sarasa Watanabe's
stage presence.

00:22:03.698 --> 00:22:04.991 position:50% align:center
It was dazzling.

00:22:14.751 --> 00:22:17.629 position:50% align:center
[KITAOUJI]
I made it. Kobe.